</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I don't get to play red as much as I like anymore, but I had a few thoughts on it.
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
   1. pvp resists vs players really not good, another tune even if you cut the effective value in half would go a long way
<br />
   2. "Non pvp flag" should be in effect during res effects, ie cant cast on other players, attack, or be attacked (would go a long way to reducing petitioning)
<br />
   3. forced bad-word filter on... once again this would reduce alot of the grief (since were all here to test our skill not our smack talking and racist tendencies)
<br />
   4. LDON style in game ranking system, by guild and by player
<br />

<br />
    * limits need to be in effect with the # of kills you can get scored per day (10 or 20ish) to prevent obvious loopholes, as well as multiple kills on the same person
<br />
    * tokens for LDON style points? to allow much needed upgrades to the weaker teams
<br />

<br />
   5.  Initiate Firiona Vie no drop ruleset (aka basically everything is tradeable except epics)
<br />

<br />
   6. Level Limits to engadge; old world must be within 6 levels and upper expansions set a 10 level or 46+ limit (aka if your 46+ anyone can attack you)
<br />

<br />
   7. Bazaar, knowledge, and nexus would remain safe zones (they all hard coded anyhow), and in addition to that time B (the graveyard) would become a non PVP zone (and the # cap needs to be changed in the GY area so it doesnt count against total allowed in timeB)
<br />

<br />
   8. Remove NPC faction assist, its just exploited anyhow
<br />

<br />
   9. Increase xp bonus WEM and player kill xp
<br />

<br />
   10. Introduce a population bonus ala planetside, lower team populations recieve a slightly higher bonus (xp, tribute wise, etc)
<br />

<br />
   11. Introduce a guild/faction team reward system based on tribute (ie +1 regen +100 hps etc), introduce guild member caps 150 to prevent entire evil side having a 800 person guild
<br />

<br />
   12. More buyable magic items to help offset non casters (snare glands, midlevel healing items ala prayers of life, damage shields, shadowstep, flash, etc) this is also to help reduce the gear gap
<br />

<br />
   13. COIN+ITEM loot, discord was a great ruleset and looking back on it, being able to loot some if not all of a persons gear was great, but for an established server 1 item isnt bad (this has to be implemented with the FV ruleset though)
<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />
Chanter/spellcaster specific ones:
<br />

<br />
Charm (double the # of counters on it to make it require more then a level 1 dispel to break it), also allow charming of players again
<br />

<br />
Rapture (increase the range, but dont allow it to stack with itself so you would have to alternate, same with bard rapture so you cant perma mez someone)
<br />

<br />
Lure Nuke (for enchanters set the resistant rate alot lower against other players, since in effect this is a mind based spell)
<br />

<br />
root (reduce the resist rate against players)
<br />

<br />
snare (reduce the resist rate against players, but allow them to mitigate it)
<br />

<br />
mana drain (increase the chanter one, remove bard focus on theirs, allow the rest of the series ie wandering mind to effect pvp)
<br />

<br />
maintain illusions (since illusion items are alot more attainable now for all factions, set them permanent again, with a % chance to break illusion each hit)
<br />

<br />
reflect (this spell is mainly pvp, but it really needs to add a % spellshield line to it, that way it becomes that much more important)
<br />

<br />
whirl/ddd (reduce the resist rate in pvp on this spell)
<br />

<br />
pets (increase the damage on pets v. players, but mitigate runspeed changes on them snare and sow type spells)
<br />

<br />
Add more pvp specific spells that have some value in PVE
<br />

<br />
Invisibility (needs an improved version that has a chance to avoid detection based on level or intelligence)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
